    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-26T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-26T05:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/8–2644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé to the Greek Government in Exile</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-26T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 26, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 26—8:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Greek 263. Telegram from Eden to Lord Moyne dated August 25 asks that Moyne
                    present armistice terms to Bulgarian delegate now at Istanbul who is being sent
                    to Cairo for this purpose. This disagrees with Department’s 71, August 25.<note
                        n="26" xml:id="d291fn26">Not printed.</note> Because of better communication
                    with Bulgaria, Steel<note n="27" xml:id="d291fn27">Christopher E. Steel, Acting
                        Counselor of the British Embassy in Egypt.</note> strongly favors
                    negotiation at Ankara and is advising London to this effect.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Murphy as 21, to Ankara and to London as 8.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
